Subject: [PATCH] mm: khugepaged: skip huge page collapse for special files
Git-commit: a4aeaa06d45e90f9b279f0b09de84bd00006e733
Patch-mainline: v5.15
References: stable-5.14.16 bsc#1193983 CVE-2021-4148 CVE-2021-47491 bsc#1224900

commit a4aeaa06d45e90f9b279f0b09de84bd00006e733 upstream.

The read-only THP for filesystems will collapse THP for files opened
readonly and mapped with VM_EXEC.  The intended usecase is to avoid TLB
misses for large text segments.  But it doesn't restrict the file types
so a THP could be collapsed for a non-regular file, for example, block
device, if it is opened readonly and mapped with EXEC permission.  This
may cause bugs, like [1] and [2].

This is definitely not the intended usecase, so just collapse THP for
regular files in order to close the attack surface.

